---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Palchat">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 pb-12 pt-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:pb-16 lg:pt-16">
    <header class="mb-8 space-y-3">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-balance text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Palchat is a playground of product ideas and tiny tools.
      </h1>
      <p class="max-w-2xl text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
        It is intentionally <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">not</span> a chat tool. The goal is to collect
        opinionated ideas and pair them with small, free utilities that help builders decide what to work on next.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-10 space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-xl">What Palchat tries to do</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300">
        <li class="flex gap-2">
          <span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-slate-400" />
          <span><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">Collect useful ideas</span> — focused on products that solo builders or small teams can realistically ship.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-2">
          <span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-slate-400" />
          <span><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">Offer tiny SaaS-style tools</span> — simple utilities (like the Idea Prioritization Tool) that are free to use in the browser.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-2">
          <span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-slate-400" />
          <span><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">Stay low-friction</span> — no logins required for core exploration, no feeds, no infinite scrolling.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10 space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-xl">Tech stack</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
        Palchat is built with a simple, scalable stack that makes it easy to add more ideas and tools over time.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">At a glance</h3>
          <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
            <li><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">Astro</span> for fast, modern pages.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">React</span> (via <code class="rounded bg-slate-800/80 px-1 py-0.5 text-[11px]">@astrojs/react</code>) for interactive components when needed.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">Tailwind CSS</span> for styling and consistent design tokens.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">PostgreSQL</span> with a pooled client and managed hosting.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">Vercel</span> for hosting, SSL, and deployments.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col justify-between gap-3">
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
            For a more visual breakdown of how these pieces fit together (by layer: UI, APIs, data, and infra), you can
            see the dedicated tech stack page.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/tech-stack"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-emerald-500/60 bg-emerald-500/10 px-3 py-2 text-xs font-medium text-emerald-200 transition hover:bg-emerald-500/20 hover:text-emerald-100 sm:text-sm"
          >
            View full tech stack
            <span aria-hidden="true" class="ml-1 text-[11px]">
              →
            </span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-xl">Get in touch</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
        If you have an idea that might fit here—or a tiny tool you wish existed—reach out and it might make its way
        into Palchat.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        You can email <a href="mailto:hello@palchat.org" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-slate-100">hello@palchat.org</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>
</Layout>
